narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Spanish 110 is a good foundational course to learn the basics. Supersite can get annoying, but overall I recommend it for anyone looking to learn the language.

I would totally recommend spanish L1 to everyone who hasn't learned spanish yet. It is incredible how much progress you make over the course of a couple month and it is a really useful and spoken language around the globe.

SPAN 110 is a great introductory Spanish course. It can be a little fast-paced in the beginning if you have no experience with Spanish. The course itself was very organized and classroom activities were fun. Maripaz was a great professor!
This class is an entry level class to Spanish. It is much fun and you can learn a lot about the language and the culture.

Spanish 110 is a great course, but is a little more work due to the fact that it meets every day. However, the course was very beneficial. I would recommend Spanish highly to any student looking to start a language at Yale.
you learn a lot. Sharp learning curve in the beginning. Come ready to play.
L1 Spanish isn't easy. The course moves fast and the tests are hard so be prepared to study every day.
